Of3PIDmPm2zccwEobtW_MFur2w_2hcH4o1GcIbPaklQv3q8JowPrijn2QGhyZ3wOheRhZNc2R6GtYpummGw9gYwa3BvCT0Hh1nKRfVKiuPBT6Fnkn4dJQHY0biuAts3teubeCQwHBpsIB0EEuvPF7_Bk3vkFTDdLdoSKkwbEJwDEt3odCXAI7OA5uwvJKxANsvYcBc2hUSzeBTJeHw6qtV1fftoLRKGRTzym0fC1bxUexZYcU94pNvKrbdKsbHp_fv1MuoVV\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating DESKeySpec usage**\\n\\nI’m considering whether using DESKeySpec with existing JDK class reflection metadata is appropriate. The agent sees it, but I’m unsure about the assertion (using getKeySpec with secret and DESKeySpec.class). While it feels a bit unnatural, the public API does allow this. It could construct DESKeySpec from PBE key bytes, which might help avoid complications with nested classes and metadata in a test class. However, I’ll still need to use Constructor#newInstance.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating security implementation**\\n\\nI'm considering using `Security.addProvider` in `@BeforeAll`, but I notice that existing tests may not. Perhaps I can pass the new `BouncyCastleProvider` directly. It seems that `SecretKeyFactory.getInstance(alg, Provider)` uses the provider object but doesn't register, which is interesting. I find that using `static final Provider BC_PROVIDER = new BouncyCastleProvider()` is fine. I also need to generate a secret with `PBEKeySpec` and include salt to produce the encoded key bytes. Exploring the potential issues with Bouncy Castle and JDK 21 is important too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5feokbsnVTXnCrqr4SP5GyLi|fc_04105273bb0441c50169fbed356b90819d86233374d14a9eac", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/BaseSecretKeyFactoryTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk15on;\n\nimport java.security.Provider;\n\nimport javax.crypto.SecretKey;\nimport javax.crypto.SecretKeyFactory;\nimport javax.crypto.spec.DESKeySpec;\nimport javax.crypto.spec.PBEKeySpec;\nimport javax.crypto.spec.SecretKeySpec;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.BouncyCastleProvider;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class BaseSecretKeyFactoryTest {\n    @Test\n    void createsRequestedByteArrayKeySpecFromPbeSecretKey() throws Exception {\n        SecretKeyFactory factory = SecretKeyFactory.getInstance(\"PBEWITHSHAANDIDEA-CBC\", bouncyCastleProvider());\n        PBEKeySpec passwordSpec = new PBEKeySpec(\n            \"correct horse battery staple\".toCharArray(),\n            new byte[] {1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 15},\n            19,\n            128);\n\n        SecretKey secretKey = factory.generateSecret(passwordSpec);\n        DESKeySpec convertedSpec = (DESKeySpec) factory.getKeySpec(secretKey, DESKeySpec.class);\n        SecretKeySpec roundTrippedSpec = (SecretKeySpec) factory.getKeySpec(secretKey, SecretKeySpec.class);\n\n        assertThat(secretKey.getAlgorithm()).isEqualTo(\"PBEwithSHAandIDEA-CBC\");\n        assertThat(secretKey.getFormat()).isEqualTo(\"RAW\");\n        assertThat(convertedSpec.getKey()).containsExactly(secretKey.getEncoded());\n        assertThat(roundTrippedSpec.getAlgorithm()).isEqualTo(\"PBEwithSHAandIDEA-CBC\");\n        assertThat(roundTrippedSpec.getEncoded()).containsExactly(secretKey.getEncoded());\n    }\n\n    private static Provider bouncyCastleProvider() {\n        return new BouncyCastleProvider();\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1675, "output": 1677, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35096, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778117924355, "responseId": "resp_0410